Author: phm87#7395
Content: If I want to stake 1600 LABS, should I split it in 64 addresses using the pos64staker script ? Or is it better to let everything in one address ? I tested with splitting to 64 addresses (UTXOs size = 4 and amount of UTXOs to send to each segid = 5) but how can we optimise these numbers for optimal staking with X labs ?

Author: ComputerGenie üë¥üèºüì¢#7004
Content:
Your minimum "sort of optimal" is 1 UTXO per segid.
this can be swayed by UTXO size though, you really need to "establish" what your ratio to staked supply is (the higher the supply the larger a UTXO likely needs to be in order to be viable) and that's more of a guessing game than anything else
My personal method usually 20 UTXOs per segid and *not* setting a pubkey, then consolidate and resplit every time my holdings hit 2x

Author: phm87#7395
Content: thank you for your advices and explanations CG

Author: ComputerGenie üë¥üèºüì¢#7004
Content:
for clarity, what I mean by "staked supply" is that if 1000 people are staking with UTXOs worth 20 and they all split their stakes across all 64 segIDs, then you will *generally* not fair as well with UTXOs of 1 coin than if you were close to their size.
Time since the UTXO was created plays a factor too, but the above is in an "all other things being equal" situation

Author: phm87#7395
Content: With 1600 coins, if I use 64 times 20 UTXO, I can set UTXO size of 1 maximum I think ... I'll try to find tools to analyse stakers in a network (I never did). I don't know if such tools exist

Author: phm87#7395
Content: but uxto size of 1 is very small

Author: ComputerGenie üë¥üèºüì¢#7004
Content: with 1600, you may have to start with 1-3 UTXOs per, see how well you do, and work it out from there

Author: ComputerGenie üë¥üèºüì¢#7004
Content: because luck is a factor, there is no "best" system to do

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: if X/coinsupply is less than 1/64, it might be best to just have it in a single utxo

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: pick the lowest staking segid and put all into a single utxo in that segid

Author: ComputerGenie üë¥üèºüì¢#7004
Content: on one chain, there was someone (I forget who) that used a **ton** of UTXOs sized 1-5 coins and did quite well

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: this way, even a small stake can have a decent change every 64 blocks

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: yes, if you have more than 1/64th the coin supply, the optimal changes a lot

Author: ComputerGenie üë¥üèºüì¢#7004
Content:
`yes, if you have more than 1/64th the coin supply, the optimal changes a lot`
I learned that with OUR; no plan I did well with on any other chain worked as well on OUR as it did on those others, partly/mostly because of small my total was
